stream
BT
/F1 10.5 Tf
14 TL
1 0 0 1 54.0 721.0 Tm (Use the main QR code first. If an Android phone or guest Wi-Fi cannot open the `.local`) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 707.0 Tm (address, use the Android/IP fallback QR code.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 676.0 Tm (During A Service) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 628.0 Tm (- Use **Start captions** when ready.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 614.0 Tm (- Use **Stop** when captions should stop.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 600.0 Tm (- Use **Blank / pause** before private prayer, pastoral details, testimony,) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 586.0 Tm (safeguarding, or anything sensitive.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 572.0 Tm (- Use **Resume** when public captions should continue.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 558.0 Tm (- Watch the microphone level meter to confirm audio is coming in.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 527.0 Tm (Translation) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 479.0 Tm (Argos Translate support is installed during setup, but translated captions stay off) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 465.0 Tm (until the operator enables them.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 434.0 Tm (Translation is experimental and may be inaccurate. Keep the active translated language) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 420.0 Tm (limit low at first. Use a qualified human interpreter where accuracy matters.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 389.0 Tm (Passwords) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 341.0 Tm (The operator password is stored outside the Church Cap folder in:) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 310.0 Tm (~/Library/Application Support/Church Cap/data/) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 279.0 Tm (On Windows, it is stored in:) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 248.0 Tm (%APPDATA%\\Church Cap\\data\\) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 217.0 Tm (It should survive Terminal restarts, Mac restarts, and app folder updates.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 186.0 Tm (If the operator is locked out:) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 155.0 Tm (./reset-operator-password.sh) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 124.0 Tm (On Windows:) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 93.0 Tm (.\\reset-operator-password.cmd) Tj
1 0 0 1 54.0 62.0 Tm (Then restart Church Cap and create a new password.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
